---
title: Chicken Sausage & Spinach Ricotta Ravioli with Tomato & Lemon
description: Mamma mia! Here’s some perfect pasta prepared at pronto speed. The sauce starts with tomato and chicken sausage that cook up quickly in the pan. Once you’ve got your water boiling for the pasta, in go the ravioli, which become al dente in a flash since they’re fresh. After that, all you gotta do is finish the creamy sauce and it’s buon appetito!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/61f04e445b14ba64871c9512-2fe03fc2.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-sausage-spinach-ricotta-ravioli-61f04e445b14ba64871c9512-143cd461.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chicken-sausage-and-spinach-ricotta-ravioli-61f04e445b14ba64871c9512
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 39 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 63 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 1880 mg
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Dice
@Roma tomato{1%unit}. Quarter @lemon{1%unit}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz}, scallion whites, and
@Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until sausage
is browned and scallions are softened, ~{3-5%minutes} (the sausage will finish
cooking in step 4).

Stir in tomato and cook until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Once water is boiling, gently add @spinach and ricotta ravioli{9%oz} to pot.
Reduce to a low simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente and
floating to the top, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

> TIP: Gently shake strainer with ravioli in it to remove as much moisture as
> possible.

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a small
splash of reserved pasta cooking water into pan with sausage mixture. Cook over
low heat, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until sausage is
cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat. Stir in @sour cream{4%tbsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} until melted and
combined. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: If needed, stir in more reserved cooking water a splash at a time until
> sauce reaches a creamy consistency.

Gently stir drained ravioli into pan with sauce. Season with salt, pepper, and
lemon juice to taste.

Divide pasta between plates or bowls. Garnish with scallion greens. Serve with
any remaining lemon wedges on the side.